issue.title: bug: App is stuck after the splash screen on Android (Huawei P20)
issue.body:
## Bug Report

### Capacitor Version
<!--
Paste the output from the `npx cap doctor` command into the code block below. This will provide the versions of Capacitor packages and related dependencies.
-->

```
Installed Dependencies:

  @capacitor/ios: not installed
  @capacitor/cli: 5.3.0
  @capacitor/core: 5.3.0
  @capacitor/android: 5.3.0
```

### Platform(s)
<!--
List the platforms that this bug affects.
-->
Android


### Current Behavior
<!--
Describe how the bug manifests. Be specific.
-->
On Huawei P20 devices apps made with Ionic Capacitor are stuck after the splash screen. After the splash screen is shown there is only a white (light mode )or black (dark mode) screen.


### Expected Behavior
<!--
Describe what the behavior should be.
-->
Apps should be working.


### Code Reproduction
<!--
To isolate the cause of the problem, we ask you to provide a minimal sample application that demonstrates the issue.
For full instructions, see: https://github.com/ionic-team/capacitor/blob/HEAD/CONTRIBUTING.md#creating-a-code-reproduction
-->
Create a Ionic Capacitor app with `ionic start` and add the Android platform. Build the app and launch on it a Huawei P20 device. The app shouldn't be working.


### Other Technical Details
<!--
Please provide the following information with your request and any other relevant technical details (versions of IDEs, local environment info, plugin information or links, etc).
-->

`npm --version` output: 8.19.3

`node --version` output: v16.19.0

### Additional Context
<!--
List any other information that is relevant to your issue. Stack traces, related issues, suggestions on how to fix, Stack Overflow links, forum links, etc.
-->
Apps made with Capacitor downloaded from the Play Store aren't working on P20 too. (e.g Burger King, Sworkit)
On other devices the apps are working as expected.

### Device Info:

```
Vendor: Huawei
Model: P20 Pro
OS: EMUI 12.0.0
WebView: Android System WebView 116.0.5845.172
```

### Logs on the working device

issue.body:
## Bug Report

### Capacitor Version
<!--
Paste the output from the `npx cap doctor` command into the code block below. This will provide the versions of Capacitor packages and related dependencies.
-->

```
@capacitor/core: 4.7.0
```
(also present in @capacitor/core: 5.x)

### Platform(s)
<!--
List the platforms that this bug affects.
-->

iOS, Android

### Current Behavior
<!--
Describe how the bug manifests. Be specific.
-->

Response headers are not added to an XHR request that is issued over the bridge when the casing does not match expectations. For example, XMLHttpRequest.prototype.getResponseHeader returns headers correctly regardless of casing.
E.g., getResponseHeader('My-Header') and getResponseHeader('my-header') should return the same value. 
CapacitorHttp XHR requests for the native-bridge must have correct casing to match the returned header. 

This means that integrations with third party libraries will break if they use the case insensitive nature of the web implementation.

### Expected Behavior
<!--
Describe what the behavior should be.
-->

Native XHR requests should check for case insensitive headers on the response object

### Code Reproduction
<!--
To isolate the cause of the problem, we ask you to provide a minimal sample application that demonstrates the issue.
For full instructions, see: https://github.com/ionic-team/capacitor/blob/HEAD/CONTRIBUTING.md#creating-a-code-reproduction
-->


### Other Technical Details
<!--
Please provide the following information with your request and any other relevant technical details (versions of IDEs, local environment info, plugin information or links, etc).
-->


### Additional Context
<!--
List any other information that is relevant to your issue. Stack traces, related issues, suggestions on how to fix, Stack Overflow links, forum links, etc.
-->
